article.headline: TCU 92, Prairie View 80
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Kevin Langford scored 31 points, including 17 in the second half, to lead TCU to a 92-80 victory over Prairie View A&M Saturday. Henry Salter added 24 points, including 18 off 3-pointers for the Horned Frogs (7-3). Brent Hackett added 11. Aaron Smith led Prairie View (2-9) with 23 points. Brian Ezeh scored 14 and Derek Johnson 11. Prairie View opened the second half with a couple of quick baskets to cut TCU's lead to 1 at 46-45. Salter hit hit three of his 3-pointers in about 90 seconds to put the Horned Frogs back up by nine. Johnson hit a layup with 12:41 left in the second half to pull Prairie View to within one for the last time and TCU went back up by nine on as Salter hit two more 3-pointers. The Horned Frogs continued to pull away, leading by as many as 15. TCU led 46-40 at the half.
